   <text>
      <body>
         <head rend="center"><title type="main"><emph rend="italic">Song</emph><emph rend="super"
                  >1</emph><note type="head" place="bottom"><emph rend="super">1</emph> Published in
                     <emph rend="italic">Columbian Herald and New Daily Advertiser</emph>
                  [Charleston, SC] (April 19, 1796), p. 4; reprinted in the same, (May 6, 1796),
                  p. 4.</note></title></head>
         
         <div1 type="stanza">
            <head rend="center">I.</head>
            <lg>
               <l>I told my Clara<emph rend="super">2</emph><note type="gloss" place="bottom"><emph
                        rend="super">2</emph> Perhaps a variant of Clarinda, the name first used by
                     Edmund Spenser in Book V of the <emph rend="italic">Faerie Queene</emph>
                     (1596).</note> tender tales,</l>
               <l>My sighs were louder than the gales,</l>
               <l>My eyes like gushing fountains flow’d,</l>
               <l>But Clara no compassion shew’d. </l>
            </lg>
         </div1>
         <div1 type="stanza">
            <head rend="center">II.</head>
            <lg>
               <l n="5">I swore, and lovers all can lie,</l>
               <l>I swore by poison I would die,</l>
               <l>Or hang me on some willow tree,</l>
               <l>Yet still she would not pity me. </l>
            </lg>
         </div1>

         <div1 type="stanza">
            <head rend="center">III.</head>
            <lg>
               <l>I vow’d to quit my native shore,</l>
               <l n="10">And never, never, see her more;</l>
               <l>Or frantic, perish on the main,</l>
               <l>Yet would not Clara ease my pain. </l>
            </lg>
         </div1>
         <div1 type="stanza">
            <head rend="center">IV.</head>
            <lg>
               <l>At length, when nothing could prevail,</l>
               <l>Nor sigh, nor tear, nor tender tale,</l>
               <l n="15">I vow’d some gentler fair to find,</l>
               <l>And Clara swore she would be kind. </l>
            </lg>
         </div1>
      </body>
